definition.value: A fatty acid methyl ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of nonadecanoic acid with methanol.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a tetradecasaccharide comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched heptasaccharide unit [linked (1->6)], and an N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl linear tetrasaccharide unit [linked (1->3)].
A member of the class of  furans used to treat  peptic ulcer disease (PUD) and gastroesophageal reflux disease.

A branched amino decasaccharide comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which is (1->4)-linked an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue, together with two beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl trisaccharide units linked (1->3) and (1->6).
A linear amino tetrasaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and beta-D-mannose residues linked sequentially (2->3), (1->4) and (1->2).

A linear amino tetrasaccharide consisting of N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl, beta-D-galactosyl, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues linked sequentially (2->3), (1->4) and (1->6).

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a dodecasaccharide derivative comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the reducing-end N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue of which is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-fucosyl residue, while to the beta-D-mannose residue are linked two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->6)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl tetrasaccharide units via (1->3) and (1->6) linkages.
An N-acylglycine in which the acyl group is specified as docosanoyl.
A ribonic acid having L-configuration.
A monosaccharide derivative that is salicylic acid in which the phenolic hydrogen is replaced by a D-glucosyl residue.
An N-acylglycine in which the acyl group is specified as tetracosanoyl.
An N-acylglycine in which the acyl group is specified as hexacosanoyl.
A member of the class of choloyl-CoAs that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of lithocholic acid.
A butan-4-olide that is dihydrofuran-2-one substituted at C-3 and C-4 by hydroxy groups (the 3S,4R-diastereomer).
A dicarboxylic acid that is 2-hydroxyhepta-2,4-diene in which the two terminal methyl groups are replaced by carboxy groups (the 2Z,4Z-geoisomer).
An oxo dicarboxylic acid that is (4Z)-hept-4-enedioic acid substituted at position 2 by an oxo group.
A 4-hydroxy-2-oxoheptanedioic acid that has S-configuration at position 4.
An androstanoid that is dehydroepiandrosterone 3-sulfate substituted by a hydroxy group at the 16alpha-position.
A 3-hydroxyicosanoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3S)-hydroxyicosanoic acid.
A member of the class of pyridines that is pyridine substituted by a (2-methylpropoxy)carbonyl and a (2-phenylethoxy)carbonyl group at positions 2 and 6 respectively.
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid that is deca-4,6-dienoic acid substituted by a hydroxy group at position 3 (the 4E,6E-stereoisomer).
A hydroxy monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of (4E,6E)-3-hydroxydeca-4,6-dienoic acid.
A 3-hydroxytetracosanoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3S)-3-hydroxytetracosanoic acid.
A 3-hydroxydocosanoyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3S)-hydroxydocosanoic acid.
A 3-hydroxy fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (3S)-3-hydroxyoleic acid.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is a dodecasaccharide derivative comprising a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose and two N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the reducing-end N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue of which is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-fucosyl residue, while to the beta-D-mannose residue are linked two N-acetyl-alpha-neuraminyl-(2->3)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-alpha-D-mannosyl tetrasaccharide units via (1->3) and (1->6) linkages.
A cholestanoid resulting from the oxidation of (25R)-3beta,26-dihydroxycholest-5-en-7-one to the corresponding carboxylic acid.
A member of the class of methylindoles that is 1-methylindole substituted at position 3 by a 3-(4-methylimidazol-5-yl)propanoyl group.

An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of beta-Gal-(1->3)-beta-GalNAc-(1->4)-[alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->8)-alpha-Neu5Ac-(2->3)]-beta-Gal-(1->4)-beta-Glc-(1<->1')-Cer; major species at pH 7.3.

label.value: signal transducer and activator of transcription 5 protein inhibitor

definition.value: Any inhibitor of signal transducer and activator of transcription 5 protein
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GD1c; major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GT2; major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GT1c; major species at pH 7.3.
A linear amino trisaccharide that consists of alpha-L-fucose, 6-sulfated beta-D-galactose and N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine units connected in sequence by (1->2) and (1->3) links, respectively.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GQ1c; major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GP1c; major species at pH 7.3.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) resulting from the deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate groups of (14Z,17Z,20Z,23Z,26Z)-dotriacontapentaenoyl-CoA.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (16Z,19Z,22Z,25Z,28Z)-tetratriacontapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (18Z,21Z,24Z,27Z,30Z)-hexatriacontapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
A polyunsaturated fatty acyl-CoA(4-) obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate functions of (20Z,23Z,26Z,29Z,32Z)-octatriacontapentaenoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
An amino trisaccharide in which an alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-D-galactosyl unit is linked (1->3) to a 6-sulfated N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine residue.
An organic sodium salt that is the disodium salt of CMP.

A branched amino pentasaccharide comprising a linear tetrasaccharide chain of alpha-D-galactose, beta-D-galactose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosamine residues linked sequentially (1->3), (1->4) and (1->6), to the beta-D-galactose residue of which is also linked (1->2) an alpha-L-fucose residue.
An amino heptasaccharide in which two alpha-L-fucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl chains are linked (1->3) and (1->6) to alpha-D-galactose.

A branched amino oligosaccharide that is an undecasaccharide derivative consisting of a linear trisaccharide of beta-D-mannose, N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosamine and N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residues all linked in sequence (1->4), to the mannosyl residue of which are linked an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl residue [via a (1->4) linkage], an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->4)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched trisaccharide unit [linked (1->3)], and an N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->2)-[N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-(1->6)]-alpha-D-mannosyl branched trisaccharide unit [linked (1->6)], while to the N-acetyl-D-glucosamine residue at the reducing end is linked (1->6) an alpha-L-fucose residue.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GP1calpha; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA(4-) oxoanion arising from deprotonation of the phosphate and diphosphate OH groups of 3-(m-hydroxyphenyl)propanoyl-CoA; major species at pH 7.3.
